div.p:
—a grains agreement which provides some price stability, relieves us of the
                        burden of carrying almost all the world’s reserves and guarantees steady US
                        export growth, combined with restraints on EC use of subsidies on exports into third country markets;

—a modus vivendi on subsidies on EC exports into the United States (cheese,
                        hams) and other subsidy practices (which could be incorporated into a
                            subsidies/CVD code);
